#: ../../S/Sturgeons-Law.rst:5
msgid "Sturgeon's Law"
msgstr "Sturgeon's Law"

#: ../../S/Sturgeons-Law.rst:7
msgid "prov\\."
msgstr "ことわざ"

#: ../../S/Sturgeons-Law.rst:9
#, python-format
msgid ""
"\"Ninety percent of everything is crud\". Derived from a quote by science "
"fiction author Theodore Sturgeon, who once said, \"Sure, 90% of science "
"fiction is crud. That's because 90% of everything is crud.\" Sturgeon "
"himself called this \"Sturgeon's Revelation\", and it first appeared in the "
"March 1958 issue of *Venture Science Fiction*\\; he gave Sturgeon's Law as "
"\"Nothing is always absolutely so.\" Oddly, when Sturgeon's Revelation is "
"cited, the final word is almost invariably changed to ‘crap’. Compare "
":ref:`Hanlons-Razor`\\, :ref:`Ninety-Ninety-Rule`\\. Though this maxim "
"originated in SF fandom, most hackers recognize it and are all too aware of "
"its truth."
msgstr ""
"「あらゆるものの90パーセントはくず」。SF作家Theodore "
"Sturgeonの引用に由来する。彼はかつてこう言った。「たしかにSFの90パーセントはくずだ。それはあらゆるものの90パーセントがくずだからだ。」Sturgeon自身はこれを「Sturgeonの啓示」と呼び、それは\\"
" *Venture Science Fiction*\\ "
"誌の1958年3月号に初めて登場した。彼はSturgeonの法則を「何ものも常に絶対的にそうであることはない」と述べた。奇妙なことに、Sturgeonの啓示が引用されるとき、最後の語はほぼ必ず‘crap(たわごと)’に変えられる。\\"
" :ref:`Hanlons-Razor`\\ 、\\ :ref:`Ninety-Ninety-Rule`\\ "
"と比較せよ。この格言はSFファンダムに由来するが、ほとんどのハッカーはこれを認め、その真実をいやというほど自覚している。"
